Cultivate Indipendent Critical Thinking, Clinical Reasoning and Problem Solving Abilities, and Develop Lifelong Learning□ 創新與領導能力
培養具有創新與領導的能力，以為專業技能或研究奠基。 Innovative and Leadership Abilities
Cultivate Innovative and Leadership Abilities in order to Develop Therapeutic Skills and Professional Research 

課程概述 Course Description
       This class introduces various groups and programs as tools for occupational therapy intervention. The goal is to help those occupational therapy students refine their critical thinking about the group activities they select and the protocols they design in related settings. Background of knowledge will be reviewed and the student will take group leadership and other group roles with instructor's guidance.This class introduces various groups and programs as tools for occupational therapy intervention. The goal is to help those occupational therapy students refine their critical thinking about the group activities they select and the protocols they design in related settings. Background of knowledge will be reviewed and the student will take group leadership and other group roles with instructor's guidance.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    students will learn
1). how to observe and communicate in a group;
2). how to construct a group for skill training;
3). how to use various group formats regarding the media use, group structure, and membership and tasks to facilitate interaction and learning in a group;
4). the knowledge of group design with the use of occupations and related theories..    

